25/08/2018, 15:51 - Gayathri: Dear Chennai Runners

Kotak Wheelchair Marathon is on September 2, 2018 (Sunday). It is OPEN for ALL runners, not just wheelchair users.

Every runner makes a contribution towards a high-quality wheelchair for persons with spinal cord injury. This is important, as at least 90% of wheelchair users use improper wheelchairs that damage health and lifestyle.

Kotak Wheelchair Marathon aspires to lead the shift towards quality in mobility devices for the disabled.

We are pleased to offer 300 running slots (21.1 km and 10 km) at Rs 500 each to members of the Chennai Runners family. You can use the discount code Kotak-250Off to avail this special offer.

Please register at www.thespinalfoundation.in

Runners will get a T Shirt, BIB, timing chip, medal, breakfast, quality photographs, inclusive running experience and feel good.

Request the elite runners of Chennai to be a part of driving the change towards quality in mobility devices for the disabled.

Please register before August 27, 2018.

Thank You

Best Regards

Vaidy

Your Fellow Half Marathon Runner
Core Team - Kotak Wheelchair Marathon Runner

26/08/2018, 14:57 - +91 99404 86127: இதுதான் இன்றைக்கு இனிப்பான செய்தி

உங்கள் சட்டைக் காலரில் உள்ள அழுக்கு எந்த சோப்பைக் கொண்டு தேய்த்தாலும் போக மறுக்கிறதா? கவலைப்படாமல் கொஞ்சம் சீனியை எடுத்து தேய்த்துப் பாருங்கள். நிச்சயமாகப் போகும். ஆக, சட்டை அழுக்கைப் போக்கும் ஒரு வேதிப் பொருளைத் தான் நாம் அள்ளி அள்ளித் தின்று கொண்டிருக்கிறோம். இந்த சீனியைச் சாப்பிட்டால் நம் குடல் என்ன பாடுபடும்?

இனிப்யை விரும்பி சாப்பிடாதவர்கள் யார் தான் இருக்க முடியும்? காலையில் எழுந்தவுடன் குடிக்கும் காப்பியிருந்து இரவு படுக்கச் செல்லும் முன் குடிக்கும் பால் வரை சீனி ஒரு ஊடுபொருளாக நமக்குள் செல்கிறது. பதார்த்தத்தில்தான் என்றில்லை; சீனியை அப்படியே அள்ளியும் சாப்பிடுகிறோம்.

இந்த வெள்ளை சீனியை எப்படித் தயார் செய்கிறார்கள் என்கிற விபரத்தை நீங்கள் தெரிந்து கொண்டீர்களானால் இனி அதைத் தொடக்கூட மாட்டீர்கள்.

குறிப்பாக, வெள்ளைச் சீனியைத் தயார் செய்ய என்னென்ன ரசயான‌ப் பொருட்கள் பயன்படுத்தப்படுகின்றன என்று பாப்போம்.

1. கரும்பிலிருந்து சாறு பிழியப்படும் நிலையில் பிளிச்சிங் பவுடர் அல்லது குளோரின் எனப்படும் கெமிக்கலை புளுயுடு பாக்டீரியா கண்ட்ரோலாக பயன்படுத்துகிறார்கள்.

2. பிழிந்த சாறு 60 சென்டிகிரேட் முதல் 70 சென்டிகிரெட் பாஸ்போரிக் ஆசிட் லிட்டருக்கு 200 மில்லி வீதம் கலந்து சூடுபடுத்தப்படுகிறது. இந்த இடத்தில் இந்த ஆசிட் அழுக்கு நீக்கியாக பயன்படுத்தப்படுகிறது.

3. இதன் பிறகு சுண்ணாம்பை 0.2 சதவிகிதம் என்கிற அளவில் சேர்த்து சல்பர்-டை-ஆக்சைடு வாயு செலுத்துகிறார்கள்.

4. 102 சென்டிகிரேட் கொதிகலனில் சூடுபடுத்தி நல்ல விட்டமின்களை இழந்து, செயற்கை சுண்ணாம்பு சத்து அளவுக்கு அதிகமாக சேர்ந்துவிடுகிறது.

5. அடுத்து, பாலி எலக்ட்ரோலைட்டை சேர்த்து தெளிகலனில் மண், சக்கை போன்ற பொருள்களாகப் பிரித்து எடுக்கப்பட்டு தெளிந்த சாறு கிடைக்கிறது.

6. சுடுகலனில் காஸ்டிக் சோடா, வாஷிங் சோடா சேர்த்து அடர்த்தி மிகுந்த ஜுஸ் தயாரிக்கப்படுகிறது.

7. மறுபடியும் சல்பர் டை ஆக்சைடும் சோடியம் ஹைட்ரோ சல்பேட்டும் சேர்க்க  படிகநிலைக்கு சீனியாக வருகிறது. சல்பர் டை ஆக்சைடு நஞ்சு சீனியில் கலந்துவிடுகிறது.

8. இப்படித் தயாரான சீனியில் எஞ்சி நிற்பது வெறும் கார்பன் என்னும் கரியே.

தயாரான நாளிலிருந்து ஆறு மாத காலத்துக்கும் அதிகமான சீனிகளை சாப்பிடக்கூடாது. காரணம், அதில் உள்ள சல்பர்டை ஆக்சைடு என்னும் ரசாயனம் மஞ்சள் நிறமாக மாறி வீரியுமுள்ள நஞ்சாக மாறிவிடுகிறது.

குடலில் மட்டுமல்ல, பல் வலி, பல் சூத்தை, குடல்புண், சளித்தொல்லை, உடல்பருமன், இதய நோய் மற்றும் சீனி வியாதி, இரத்த அழுத்தம் போன்ற பெரிய வியாதிகள் அனைத்துக்கும் இதுதான் பிரதான காரணியாக அமைகின்றது.

ஆலைகளில் தயாரான வெள்ளை சீனி சாப்பிடுவதை நிறுத்திவிட்டு, வெல்லம், பனங்கட்டி, நாட்டுச் சர்க்கரைகளை எவ்வளவு வேண்டுமானாலும் சாப்பிடலாம். இதனால் உங்களுக்கு ரத்த அழுத்தமோ, இதய நோயோ, சர்க்கரை வியாதியோ வராது.

This is true so Can we  avoid
நண்பர்களே இன்றய ஊடகங்களால்
மறைக்கப்பட்ட சதி எனவும் கூறலாம்
பணத்திற்காக நம் பாமர
மக்களுக்கு இழைக்கப்பட்ட அநீதி.......!

-it’s not just about getting a lot of exercise: it’s getting it consistently. The more consistent you are, the lower your resting heart rate.
- Sitting all week and then blowing yourself out on the weekend is not a great approach.
-Too much sleep might actually be bad for you.

... Happy to get views of the informed....Regards, AB

Steve Jobs' last words
He died a billionaire at 56yrs of Pancreatic Cancer and here are his last words on the sick bed:

"I reached the pinnacle of success in the business world. In others’ eyes my life is an epitome of success.

However, aside from work, I have little joy. In the end, wealth is only a fact of life that I am accustomed to.

At this moment, lying on the sick bed and recalling my whole life, I realize that all the recognition and

wealth that I took so much pride in, have paled and become meaningless in the face of impending death.

You can employ someone to drive the car for you, make money for you but you cannot have someone to bear the sickness for you.

Material things lost can be found. But there is one thing that can never be found when it is lost – "Life".

When a person goes into the operating room, he will realize that there is one book that he has yet to finish reading – "Book of Healthy Life".

Whichever stage in life we are at right now, with time, we will face the day when the curtain comes down.

Treasure Love for your family, love for your spouse, love for your friends...

Treat yourself well. Cherish others.

As we grow older, and hence wiser, we slowly realize that wearing a $300 or $30 watch - they both tell the same time...

Whether we carry a $300 or $30 wallet/handbag - the amount of money inside is the same;

Whether we drive a $150,000 car or a $30,000 car, the road and distance is the same, and we get to the same destination.

Whether we drink a bottle of $300 or $10 wine - the hangover is the same;

Whether the house we live in is 300 or 3000 sq ft - loneliness is the same.

You will realize, your true inner happiness does not come from the material things of this world.

Whether you fly first or economy class, if the plane goes down - you go down with it...

Therefore.. I hope you realize, when you have mates, buddies and old friends, brothers and sisters, who you chat with, laugh with, talk with, have sing songs with, talk about north-south-east-west or heaven and earth, .... That is true happiness!!

Five Undeniable Facts of Life :
1. Don't educate your children to be rich. Educate them to be Happy. So when they grow up they will know the value of things not the price.

2. Best awarded words in London ... "Eat your food as your medicines. Otherwise you have to eat medicines as your food."

3. The One who loves you will never leave you for another because even if there are 100 reasons to give up he or she will find one reason to hold on.

4. There is a big difference between a human being and being human.
Only a few really understand it.

5. You are loved when you are born. You will be loved when you die. In between, You have to manage!

NOTE: If you just want to Walk Fast, Walk Alone! But if you want to Walk Far, Walk Together!

Six Best Doctors in the World
1. Sunlight

This free registration is basically to have the profiles of our runners and for easy communication with in the group.

This one time registration also helps to pre populate data for any event CR events.

This data will also help in communicating all CR and CRPP events seamlessly to you 

The data collected will be secured and used only for CR and CRPP related events.

Please note that this is different from the paid membership registration. The paid membership will be continued separarely as usual. 

Please use this link and complete this mandatory registration process by 4th September. (It will just take a min).

Entire town kids to elderly all were along the running route to cheer up the runners !

Aid stations / race arrangements were top notch....you have to experience the Shayadri hills and the hospitality of Satara people !

Even local police & politicians all were there to cheer up the runners !

*The only problem is thr, 407 meters of ascent on the trail !*

03/09/2018, 19:06 - Mandakini: *Krishna* was born in the darkness of the night, in the locked confines of a jail.

However, at the moment of his birth, all the guards fell asleep, the chains were broken and the barred doors gently opened.

Similarly, as soon as *Krishna (Chetna, awakening )* takes birth in our heart, all darkness *( Negativity )* fades out automatically.

All chains *( Ego, I, Me, Myself )* are broken.

And all prison doors we keep ourselves in *( Caste, Religion, Profession, Relations etc )* are opened. 

And that is the real *Message And Essence* of Janmashtmi.

Happy *Janmashtmi*

6. You can do these compulsory rides any days

 PGH to viveks and back (12k) 
 PGH to TTD and back(16k)

*Option 2*

Date/Time
Date(s) - 30/09/2018
5:00 AM - 8:00 AM

Location
Marina Light House

Categories

LSoM 13.1

We are back with the nineteenth edition of the – MINNALS.LSoM.13.1 #TheBestMilesofMadras on Sunday, 30th September 2018 at 5:00 a.m.

Thanks to everyone who have made the previous editions a grand success. This edition, as usual, is free of cost thanks to our generous sponsors.

Starting and ending at the Lighthouse, you will run 21.1 km past a host of heritage monuments & beautiful landmarks along the breezy, scenic Marina Beach. This shall be a supported run with 5 support stations serving water and some basic supplies.

Summertime is just around the corner and the heat effects are already being felt. Anyone who needs special care during long distance running, we request you to take precautions and if need be not run during the hot summer season.

Please set a reminder for #MINNALS.LSoM.13.1 at 0500 hours for last Sunday of this month on 30.09.2018

30/09/2018, 14:31 - Crpp Karthik: Message from an another group ..take care when you are cycling....

Guys If you are cycling, it is always best to ride with a group. 
Yesterday, Abirami was cycling in ECR. She generally rides with a group, and she started with a group yesterday too. For a few mins period she was alone while a motor bike came alongside and the pillion rider kicked her back wheel. She flew and fell. She had a head injury and blood loss. Luckily, nothing serious and she is recovering now in the hospital. 

This happened in ECR but none of the roads are safe. 
Just ride in groups.

02/10/2018, 12:47 - +91 99406 66025: These are the strong views of a Kerala woman on the Sabarimala verdict. This is not much about Constitutionality, but is worth looking at:

#Whatsapp_Share...

While browsing i came across this open letter by a woman in #Kerala.

Mr Naushad Ahmad Khan, have you travelled in an air plane? There while giving security instructions, they say, fix your own safety mask first before helping others. I request you to fix women rights problem in your own religion first before helping other religions.

I am a Hindu woman from Kerala and I don’t want to go to Sabarimala. You will find hundreds of thousands of us in Kerala and elsewhere. Highly educated professionals, writers, etc. who will agree with me. Why? Because, Kerala Hindu women have temples and festivals exclusively for themselves. Ours was a matriarchal society where only the women inherited.

We have a temple where once a year the priests there will wash the feet of every woman devotee who comes there because a woman is the representation of the Goddess. We have a temple in Mannarashala where the priests are exclusively women, We have Thiruvathira, which is an exclusively women’s festival and no men allowed in the vicinity. We have Pongala a pooja where lakhs and lakhs of women take part in it at Tiruvananthapuram. Since the temple cannot hold all these vast numbers, Trivandrum literally shuts down and it’s streets are full of women. Yes, exclusively women.

Contrary to that, Sabarimala is the one place in Kerala which is exclusively for men. This is where our men go together. It’s a male bonding thing like fathers and sons, brothers, uncles, grandfathers, all the male members in a family or community or friends. The whole community irrespective of caste, wealth, creed joins in including the women. Yes, many of us keep fast with the men in our family. Also women of young age and older ones above 60 are allowed inside Sabarimala, which is never shown by media. This is done because Lord Ayyappa was a brahmachari, which, pseudo secular morons fail to understand.

These forty days are a source of great joy and peace for us. In many homes, it is the only time of the year when men don’t drink, no non-veg food, every one gets up very early in the morning around 4:00 am, bathe, do their pooja, visit the nearest temple, the family gets together and it brings family members in together.

Our men don’t do this bonding by drinking, drugs or whoring, Instead it is through 40 days of detox. Every one is in it. The women as well.

There is peace in society because many alcoholics are detoxing. There is a bond not only in the family but in the community. You go for bhajans in the evening. Again the family goes together. The community gets together, very important in this day and age when everyone is working especially in Kerala.

After 40 days the men go to Sabarimala, sometimes taking their aged mothers with them and maybe the older children including girls who haven’t yet menstruated.

The women have the home to themselves. Three days or until the men come back to do as they please. What do they call this is modern terms? Yes, men having their own space and women their own space and time out. Well, we have been doing this for a long time—keeping our cultural ethos and values in mind while doing so.

So request all the pseudo secular people, media and peaceful minority to mind their own business and work on women equality in their society, which is indeed in a shameful state. Please mind your own business and let us do the same.

A True Indian Woman 🙏🙏

12/10/2018, 19:45 - Jd: https://www.townscript.com/e/break-the-barrier-by-chennai-runners-000401/booking


Running is one of the best forms of exercise. It improves cardio vascular fitness, strengthens bones and muscles, helps improve mental health and so on and so forth. 
Having said all this there are several fears and myths associated with running. Will running damage my joints? I have an existing health issue, can I run? I have had a major surgery, should I and when should I run?
Hear from people who have broken barriers to run, hear them share their experiences and understand the right way to approach running. 
The panel has runners, coach and a doctor. Join this highly interactive panel discussion.

16/10/2018, 13:48 - +91 96770 88143: Hi all....please be mindful of some safety measures while running:
(re-sending this again especially for newbees)

1. Please avoid wearing gold chains/bracelets fancy stuff that ll attract thiefs/snatchers' attention. This is applicable to gents and ladies.
2. Avoid listening to music while running. Your attention to traffic and things around u are far more important than music.
3. Don't carry your phone on hand while running. Its easy prey for snatchers to grab and scoot.
4. Try to run facing the traffic. Its relatively safe that way.
5. Please be alert to the surroundings all the time more so when its dark.
6. Running in group (rather than solo) ensures safety to some extent.
7. We can only take preventive measures to protect ourselves from anti-social elements.
8. Take care and happy running.

27/10/2018, 08:31 - +91 98404 43410: *Incident happened during our group ride today (27th Oct)*

We regrouped at 2nd pitstop Gemini, Semmimozhi poonga, as 3 new bie riders decided to return from Marina due to time constraints, we decided to halt at GS Uturn for a group pic and proceeded around 5.47am with me Sweeping the group.

According to individual speed,the group split into 2 or 3 riders group, within 5 min, we saw 3 riders halting mid way. One of them being victim of a wallet snatch. Just after Woodlands flyover and b4 CitiCenter at RK Salai this incident happened as the three were riding in tandem, a bike with two person followed them and fixed our rider as vulnerable target.. they tried grabbing his mobile phone from the pouch on handle bar, struggled to take with little confrontation by rider, but the bikers somehow unlocked the zip of pouch & fleed away with his wallet & also pushing him down. 

Luckily the rider escaped with few scratches in elbows. Significant loss of money 😒

*Avoid carrying too much cash or valuables, costly mobiles, or any other gadgets*

*Please ride in groups, Tag along with fellow riders*

*Reach on time to start point and respective pitstops*

*Message as u start & reach back home so the organizers know that u are joining the ride.*

29/10/2018, 20:34 - Crpp Karthik: Dear All,

Food, shelter and dress are the three basic needs for the survival of humans beings.

Thuli is an organisation involved in providing dresses to the lesser previleged people of our society. They have a shop in Adayar where the needy can walk in and take the dresses of their choice, *free of cost !*

You may find more about, Thuli in this video,
https://youtu.be/pOrGE4J1qUc

We did a collection drive few months back & got overwhelming response. Thanks to you all, the needy people could get a car full of dresses and other stuffs.

This festive season, Thuli needs dresses for kids in the age group of, 5-15 years. 

Please note this is an independent effort and the donation is at your discretion. Request you all to join hands with Thuli to bring more smiles to the needy, this festive season !

*We request you to donate gently used kids clothes, you may also donate new clothes, if you wish to.*

*We will collect these dresses on Saturday post run, like we did last time.*

Thanks & regards,

Chandrani &
Karthik

30/10/2018, 17:14 - +91 99761 47435: Mahatma Gandhi said “the day a woman can walk freely on the roads at night, that day we can say that India has achieved true independence”.

National Crime Records Bureau Statisitcs 2016 reveals there is a steady increase in crimes against women with an intention to outrage the modesty of women.

Woman runners do come across incidents every now and then during the run. Added to this are cases of chain snatching and other offences.

Changing the mindset of society is a long drawn process. Should women get scared and stop living or should they equip themselves with life skills?

Chennai Runners in association with Greater Chennai Police has come forward to help women who are early morning road users by offering a martial art workshop.

Kravmaga is an Israeli self defence system used by their military. It is a combination of various martial arts. It is considered to be a street self defence system and helps to react quickly when there is any incident.

The course instructor is putting together a 2 hour workshop that will teach some practical self defence techniques with tips on how to stay safe.

This will be held on the second Saturday of November, 10.11.2018, at Rajarathinam Stadium, Egmore between 6AM and 8AM.

02/11/2018, 20:37 - Crpp Karthik: Dear All,

Food, shelter and dress are the three basic needs for the survival of humans beings.

Thuli is an organisation involved in providing dresses to the lesser previleged people of our society. They have a shop in Adayar where the needy can walk in and take the dresses of their choice, *free of cost !*

You may find more about, Thuli in this video,
https://youtu.be/pOrGE4J1qUc

We did a collection drive few months back & got overwhelming response. Thanks to you all, the needy people could get a car full of dresses and other stuffs.

This festive season, Thuli needs dresses for kids in the age group of, 5-15 years. 

Please note this is an independent effort and the donation is at your discretion. Request you all to join hands with Thuli to bring more smiles to the needy, this festive season !

*We request you to donate gently used kids clothes, you may also donate new clothes, if you wish to.*

*We will collect these dresses on Saturday post run, like we did last time.*

Thanks & regards,

Chandrani &
Karthik

No.of participants : 5

Each Team to have 3 runners, 1 cyclist and 1 puzzle solver.
You have to Crack the clues and spot the place. Runners and cyclists will have a different set of clues.
Puzzle solver gets a different one and he solves them at Corporation Ground.
Runners and cyclist head to the ground once they crack the clues and finish with the puzzle solver. Team that solves max clues in 1 hr is the winner.

*The Best Duo* 
No. of participants : 2 
Fathers with lil boys participate in this Run. It's just a Fun Run.. Run around corporation ground 3 times with your son/lil one.

*No Pain No Gain*: 
Test for strength. ( Macho Men from each team participate..)

No of participants :3
Each 1 takes up 1 task.. Plank, push ups, squats 

*Tug of war*  : 
No. of participants : Whole team

FAQ's 
1. Prices : ₹800 for 5/10/21km category and ₹1000 for Parent&Kid catefory.
2. What else runner gets? A goodie bag with a water bottle, Rs.500 voucher of Little Italy,  Introductory Free 3 washes from Big Laundry, and vouchers of various brands. We may get goodies like wrist band, cap, etc which we will intimate as and when it keeps coming.
3. What is Bib? An instrument to record your run timing
4. Both parent&Kid will get jersey and bibs ? YES, they will.
5. Flag off timings: Tentatively 4.30am for 21km, 5.15am for 10km and 5.45am for 5km. Parent & Kid 6:15 am.

Bib s to be collected one day in advance for Decathlon - Ramee Mall in Hyaat hotel mouth road

07/12/2018, 17:21 - +91 95001 33229: இப்போதெல்லாம் 50 வயதைத் தொட்டவுடன், உடலளவிலும் மனதளவிலும் இனி தன்னால் பெரிதாக ஒன்றும் செய்ய முடியாது என்று பலர் கற்பிதம் செய்து கொள்கிறார்கள்.

50 வயதிலேயே ரிட்டயர்மென்ட் மனநிலையை நோக்கி பயணிக்கற பலரை இப்போது பார்க்க முடிகிறது.

50 வயதுக்கு பிறகுதான் ஒரு பலமான மூளையோடு நாம் பயணிக்க ஆரம்பிக்கறோம்.

10,000 கி.மீ பதவுசா வண்டியை ஓட்டுங்க, அதுக்கப்பறம் வண்டி ஸ்மூத்தா இருக்கும் என்பார்கள்.....  50 வயதும் அப்படிதான்..... பல விஷயங்களில் அனுபவப்பட்டு, தெளிந்து, வாழ்க்கையை புரிதலோடு பார்க்கிற பருவம் இந்த இரண்டாவது இன்னிங்ஸ்தான்!!!

50 வயதுக்கு மேல் செய்ய வேண்டிய சில அவசியமான விஷயங்கள்.

1.  புதியதை தேடுங்கள்:  சிலர் “பார்ன் வித் ஏ சில்வர் ஸ்பூனாக” இருக்கலாம்..... 50களில் வாழ்க்கையில் ஓரளவு செட்டில் ஆகியிருந்தால் இந்த உந்துசக்தி குறைந்து போகும்..... சோம்பேறித்தனம் சொம்போடு உட்கார்ந்து மொக்கை போடும்...... எனவே புதிய உந்துசக்தியை உருவாக்க புதிதான ஒன்றைக் கையிலெடுங்கள்...... உங்களை சுறுசுறுப்பாக வைத்துக்கொள்ள தோதாக ஒன்றைச் செய்யுங்கள்.

2.  இளைஞர்களோடு பழகுங்கள்:  50 வயதுக்கு மேற்பட்ட ஆட்களோடு உட்கார்ந்து அங்கிள் அசோசியஷனை உருவாக்காதீர்கள்...... உங்களை விட வயதில் குறைவானவர்களோடு பழகுங்கள்!!!!! உங்களுக்கு 25 வயதில் இருந்த, அவர்களிடம் இருக்கும், அந்த எனர்ஜி உங்களுக்கும் கிடைக்கும்.....
அங்கிள் அசோஷியனில் உட்கார்ந்தால் இன்னும் வயசாகும்!!!

3.  அழகாக உடை உடுத்துங்கள்:  அழகான உடைகளை தேர்வு செய்யுங்கள்..... காமா சோமா என்று ஒரு காம்பினேஷனில் உடை போட்டுக் கொண்டு திரியாதிர்கள்!!!!! 50 வயதில் நரையும் வழுக்கையும் அழகுதான்!!!!! உலகின் அழகான நிறைய பேரை ஈர்க்கின்றவர்களில் 50+கார்கள்தான் அதிகம்!!!!

4.  பயணம் செல்லுங்கள்:  உடனே 50+ ஆட்கள் பத்துபேரை கூட்டிக் கொண்டு கோயில் கோயிலாக கிளம்பிவிடாதீர்கள்!!!!! இளைஞர்களையும் சேர்த்துக் கொள்ளுங்கள்...... வித்தியாசமான இடங்களுக்கு செல்லுங்கள்!!!!! வேறுபட்ட மனிதரோடு உரையாடுங்கள்..... திசையறியா பயணங்கள் செல்லுங்கள்..... இல்லையென்றால், 50 வயதில் அங்கிள் ஆன நீங்கள், 60 வயதில் கிழவனாகி விடுவீர்கள்!!!

5.  நிறைய படியுங்கள்:   மூளைக்கு தீனிபோட, நிறைய படியுங்கள்..... தேர்வு செய்து படியுங்கள்!!!  புதிய நவீன சிந்தனையாளர்களின் புத்தகங்களை வாசியுங்கள்..... அவர்கள் பேச்சை கேளுங்கள்.

அறிவுப் பகிர்தல் நடக்கும் இடங்களில் எல்லாம் இருக்கும்படியாக பார்த்துக் கொள்ளுங்கள்!!!

மேற்சொன்ன விஷயங்களை செய்தால் 50+ ஆரோக்கியம் பற்றிக் கவலைப்பட வேண்டியதில்லை!!!!!

மூளையும் மனசும் சரியாக இயங்க ஏற்பாடு செய்துவிட்ட பிறகு ஆரோக்கியத்தில் என்ன பிரச்சனை வரப் போகிறது?????

எப்போதுமே முதல் இன்னிங்கசை விட இரண்டாம் இன்னிங்கஸ்தான் வெற்றி தோல்வியை நிர்ணயிப்பதில்    பெரும் பங்கு வகிக்கறது..... நீங்கள் 50+ கார்ராக இருந்தால் தாமதிக்காதீர்கள்!!!!

இது உங்கள் ஆட்டம்..... துவங்குங்கள்!!!!!

22/12/2018, 19:52 - +91 98408 40466: <Media omitted>
22/12/2018, 19:52 - +91 98408 40466: 15 Dec 2018!

SPCM 2019 is around the corner. The runners are slowly getting into the tapering mood. The preparation fever has already reached its high and the race day excitement is slowly kicking in. To spice it all up, CRPP, CRNN and CRTT decided to do something fun and exciting at a public place – as a promo/awareness campaign.
5PM Ashok Nagar Metro station: Pillar Pacers and Nugambakkam Nitros team started checking in. Excitement was in the air – some are going to perform, and the others are equally excited to watch the performance. A Zumba session was organized at level 1 of Ashok Nagar metro, conducted by Bhuvan of CRPP. Runners and their families – kids, spouses had fun shaking leg for the tunes and repeating what Bhuvan did. It was fun all around – people capturing the moments and movements. Some were checking out metro features – the free cycle program etc. Once the dance was over, all moved over to platform (thanks to Chennai Metro for giving group ticket. With a swift, smooth ride the team reached the Vadapalani Metro Station. In the meantime, CRTT team started from Anna Nagar metro station and had reached Vadapalani station.
6 PM Vadapalani Metro station: Commuters were crisscrossing on a Saturday evening, going to the mall, movie or returning from there. A group of people (some in running tees, no points for guessing that 😉) were moving around the first-floor level of the station and suddenly… Music started blaring, people falling in line and the dance began! The TT team went first with their moves, enthralling everyone there. Latest music numbers, quick cool moves and everyone was thrilled. When their performance ended with a bang, the Pillar Pacers and Nitros team came in as if saying “wait, it’s not over yet”. They set the floor on fire with peppy numbers and rapid moves, capturing everyone’s attention! For a short-time the station was filled with high energy – music and dance! All the commuters stopped and was pleasantly surprised to see the flash mob dance. Towards the end, everyone joined the floor and it ended with “Gumthalakadi Gummaava… chennaina Summaavaa!!”
It was a great evening, the team walked back to respective platforms (to Ashok Nagar/Anna Nagar), continuing with selfies, jokes and jibes – soaking the metro station with gaiety!
Note: Metro may be the best way to reach the start point on the SPCM event day. The event is expected to start near Nandanam which has a metro station. The metro is now well connected within Chennai with new routes/lines opened. This could solve your parking, traveling and traffic woes!
Thanks to Mr. Sateesh Prabhu of Metro who got all required permissions for using the metro station space. Thanks to A2B for providing snacks/refreshments at a short notice.

#SPCM2019 #ChennaiMarathon #NammaChennai  #NammaMarathon  #NammaMetro #CRPP
#Towertwisters  #Flashmob #RunnersDance  #UseMetro #LetsMakeChennaiRun #NungambakkamNitros

22/12/2018, 23:06 - +91 98404 43410: *_Registrations are OPEN for the Aalam Deepam Chennai Duathlon - 2019_*

*AALAM DEEPAM CHENNAI DUATHLON 2019* is organized by WCCG-Chennai Cyclists for a cause. 
The registration fees collected from the event goes towards construction of building (Kitchen, Dining) for Home of Hope, Pakkam. Currently, the children of the home are having their food in their dormitories. We request you to extend your philanthropist support to help the children to lead a healthy life. We encourage participants to run and cycle along with their family and friends to keep good health and take part for a cause. 

_Duathlon Date - 3rd Feb, 2019_
_Reporting time - 4.30AM at Olcott Memorial School, Besant Nagar_

*Categories & Registration Fee* - 
*DEEPAM OLYMPIC Individual*
10km running and 40km cycling- INR 599
*DEEPAM SPRINT – Individual*
(5km running and 20km cycling) - INR 599

*Deepam Team Relay: Doubles (Olympic &Sprint)*
(Team Relay events will have two people in one team. One person run and one person Ride)
*DEEPAM TEAM RELAY OLYMPIC*
10km running and 40km cycling – INR 1099
*DEEPAM TEAM RELAY SPRINT*
5km running and 20km cycling - INR 1099

*AALAM DEEPAM CHENNAI DUATHLON 2019* is organized by WCCG-Chennai Cyclists for a cause. 
The registration fees collected from the event goes towards construction of building (Kitchen, Dining) for Home of Hope, Pakkam. Currently, the children of the home are having their food in their dormitories. We request you to extend your philanthropist support to help the children to lead a healthy life. We encourage participants to run and cycle along with their family and friends to keep good health and take part for a cause. 

_Duathlon Date - 3rd Feb, 2019_
_Reporting time - 4.30AM at Olcott Memorial School, Besant Nagar_

*Categories & Registration Fee* - 
*DEEPAM OLYMPIC Individual*
10km running and 40km cycling- INR 599
*DEEPAM SPRINT – Individual*
(5km running and 20km cycling) - INR 599

*Deepam Team Relay: Doubles (Olympic &Sprint)*
(Team Relay events will have two people in one team. One person run and one person Ride)
*DEEPAM TEAM RELAY OLYMPIC*
10km running and 40km cycling – INR 1099
*DEEPAM TEAM RELAY SPRINT*
5km running and 20km cycling - INR 1099

Register here..

GET INSPIRED
Shillong: Meet The 36-Yr-Old Working Mother Who Completed The Highest Ultra-Marathon In The World
Rikynti Marwein India
September 11th, 2018 / 5:53 PM

Rephica Becky Pde
On Sunday, September 9, Rephica Becky Pde, a 36-year-old working mother from Shillong, became the first Indian woman to stand tall at number two position in the Khardung La Challenge (72 km), the highest ultra-marathon in the world.

While the marathon is counted among the toughest and most challenging endurance races, for Pde it was a moment of pride as she completed the marathon in 12 hours 28 minutes despite snowfall and treacherous weather.

“Oxygen level is below 50 percent and it becomes very hard for a person to walk there, let alone run,” Pde described her experience to Highland Post. “The roads were wet and bad, it was snowing, I was wet and freezing. My hands went numb,” she said.

Rephica Becky Pde
The winners of the Khardung La Challenge
Becky said that though the weather sapped away her confidence during the race, her passion for running did not die. “At one point I thought my hands will fall off, but I managed to regain confidence after getting a jacket from the support crew,” she said.


“I knew it was the toughest run as 33 km was uphill to Khardung point. So I trained every day for months before the event as running has always been my passion,” Pde said.

Being the second position holder in the race that pushes the limits of even the toughest runners, Becky also becomes the only woman to run back to back races.

Before the challenge, Pde ran the 21 km Kargil International and came first in women category on September 2 and on September 9, the Leh Ladakh full marathon with 42 km.

 

Rephica Becky Pde
Rephica Becky Pde
It may be mentioned that the Khardung La Challenge is amongst the toughest endurance races for the serious runner who wants to push his or her limits to the extreme. The harsh conditions make this extremely tough as runners have to run approximately 60 kms of the race at 17,680 feet.

Pde said that the run had made her resolve stronger and she would now participate in marathons all over the country. Pde is among a few women ultra-marathon runners in the country. An ultra-runner covers a distance of 50km and above.


“Marathon is a mental game. Train your mind before your legs,” said Pde.

The Logical Indian applauds Rephica for achieving this feat and salutes her passion.

_To celebrate the anniversary we will have Kid's special cycling event_ 

All riders , please do join the kids to show them how to ride. After all they are our future and let them know greener, eco friendly and healthy way of life with cycling. 

(Note : Cyclist with no kids can also join the ride)

Kids... Come on ride during the event and show your talent to your parents, friends and relatives. 

Event Date - 5th Jan 2019

_5:45AM - Reporting Time_

_6:00AM - 7:30AM

2.5KM Route :
https://www.strava.com/activities/1411006262

5KM Route :
https://www.strava.com/activities/1411041046

Get back home with happy ride memories. 

_*Clicks* taken during the event will be shared in Facebook WCCG page_

_Soft copy *certificates* will be shared within a week of the event date_

_*Snacks* will be provided to kids_

*Rules:*
1. Helmet compulsory
2. Cycles to be arranged by self, event doesn't provide cycles/rental coordination.
3. Kid has to be accompanied by adult rider.
4. Adult accompanying riders to ensure their kids safety.

Please join the *Whatsapp group* if you are planning to join *Ride with Kids-2019* at Bessie.
https://chat.whatsapp.com/FPbn9dVwJoM9jvMLh2nk1S

04/01/2019, 17:05 - +91 93804 14631: *📣📣📣All SPCM Runner please read through the below📣📣📣*

Pts to remember before a Run

Few basics for new runners.
(DON'T MISS POINTS 16-20) 😃

*Very important pt 22*

1. Eat and sleep well on Fri and Sat. No late nights. No Mall-suthing, NO binge-eating, NO new foods/drinks

2. Clip your toe nails and finger nails

3. Charge your Garmin before you hit bed

4. Do light stretches throughout the day

5. Eat carbohydrates 

6. Avoid meat previous night dinner

7. Drink some extra water on Fri and Sat. At least 2-3 more glasses than usual

8. Try 1 bottle of Gatorade on Sat. Sip thru the day and not as one gulp😀

9. Wear comfortable dri fit clothes for the race. Strictly NO new clothes (incl socks, inners, etc). If ur wearing event T wash it 😃

10. Eat something light or drink milk/coffee in the morning. Empty stomach running is a no-no 

11. Reach the race venue by 45 mins before race start Time. Need time to be relaxed and warmed up

12. Do only your routine warm up exercises and not anything new, before the race (don't start new stuff or jumping that the race organizers may be doing)

13. Reach the start point 10-15 mins early. Find a comfortable spot... Being in the middle could lead to jostling that may irritate you

14. Start slow and steady...speed is for the end, not at the start. Else you may burn out too fast before warming up enough

15. It is rare to get dehydrated, despite the fear. So, don't drink too much water on the way. Sip half glass at water points if you need to. Water points exist every 2-3 kms. No need to carry a bottle. 

16. Enjoy the Run, the crowd, the noise, the pain, everything. That is the experience you have been training for! Don't miss it.

17. Remember what defines success is'finishing the race'... Not running fast. The race is really with your mind-not other participants!

18. Do cool down stretches after the race. It will help you avoid injuries and soreness

19. What you drink or eat, within 20 mins after finishing the race, gets fully absorbed by the body (like a sponge). So, have good and healthy stuff (juice, fruit etc)

20. Don't forget the selfies and the celebration with your friends at the venue

21. Don’t try anything new at hydration station like Gel etc. 

22. *If u feel any kind of discomfort that doesn’t go away nothing wrong in quitting the race. Their is always another one. Remember your family is waiting for you. Don’t take any unnecessary risk. Visit the nearest medical facility or call out to a volunteer without delay *

22. Do a Mild recovery run next morning. 2-3 km very relaxed jog!!

ENJOY. GOOD LUCK.

Happy Running

04/01/2019, 19:32 - +91 98403 57510: The motor mouth runner syndrome

Repeating from last year for newbie runners benefit (approved by the RD :) )

Posted in FB :

OK folks  , the countdown for the big one -SPCM19  has started ,and am sure many of you have already finished hard core prep and planning. But folks, be ready to hear everyone who has run before advice you on everything from how to pick your pace to your nose. Basically there are these categories of advices.

The Norukku Theeni guys 

They will talk the most because they just completed their arduous 2 k marathon yesterday and by now they are experts on everything about running including how they overcame stiff challenges like moving both their feet at different times and how they survived 3 children,5 bosses and two marriages and still ran.Lots of “noise” like norukku theeni

The Goli Soda guys

Refreshing talkers, energise you instantly, semma fizz but not sure about content, just like the soda  They will subtlety make you realise you don't belong yet to their league buy throwing words like cadence, pronation,landing ( as if its a flight). You smile and look at them with awe but don't take them seriously.

The Full Meals guys

 Beware, this notorious set will surely give you indigestion within 3 mins. You think they are talking healthy as they keep mentioning "Sub" all the time  No its not Subway food, for them life is about telling all you innocent victims about their sub 4,sub 3 ,sub servient, sub cutaneous, sub lime,SUBba matteru They measure their lives by running ultra marathons on FB, Selfie tsunamis ,whose budgets for marathons and shoes is as expensive as your dream 3BHK on boat club road.Their language,if they ever give you the honour of hearing their transcendental talk, will be a combination of Arnab on drugs launching Shashi Tharoor’s biography with a foreword by Nithyananda and Chetan Bhagat

They will teach you how you can use your left eye to control the small toe on your right leg when running. They use garmin while coughing, to plan pace/calorie optimization of their phlegm. Use your fastest legs in running away from them

The Payasam guys

The final set is the payasam .Very sweet, no noise, no one notices but no one forgets. They have quietly been practicing, working hard, and conquering many marathons with minimum fuss, like the aroma of our next door Bhai Kadai Biryani, you may not see it but surely feel it. Ask them how they did it, they will hesitatingly say " Nothing, just keep running " .Now stick to this. And enjoy your run!

-Dr Marathonayagam

09/01/2019, 10:40 - +91 98403 57510: 42.2 is tough it will make you cry
But you ain't going down without a try
And in midst of cramps and endless fatigue
You will try an find your runners high
And should you fail to get that high
Beer is there cause 17th ain't dry
So say a little prayer and look at the sky
See that lovely bird fly so high
And if the birdie shat on your eye
You wipe your face and say
Thank God pigs dont fly.

9 days to race day..
(This is elaboration and twisted version of something I read somewhere.. The disclaimer/credits are hereby given)
By Ankit Khandelwal
09/01/2019, 10:40 - +91 98403 57510: Stages of SCMM full : #slowrunner 

Disclaimer : Any one who runs fast.....please maaf kar dena .....this is for slow runners .....😢😢😢😢😢

0km : start line : u r the world and u r about to conquer with all positive energy.

3 kms : you are on Marine Drive ; the home ground to all mumbai runners.

5kms : Wilson on right.

6kms : close to babulnath on left and soam( the best gujarathi food restaurant)on right.

7kms : u begin u r ascent towards the first flyover kemps corner.....u r feeling fresh.....hmers elites are now nearby. Malabar hill on the left....

8km : u see Antillia .....what a wastage of money😢😢😢😢😢

9kms : the descent on peddar road.....this gonna be tough when u come back at 35kms..... okay move down to mahalaxmi and  haji Ali dargah on left.....piya haji Ali. Heera Panna on ur right.

Move on.....on the road.....the race course.....the HMers are on their way. Hi hello the shouting of names.....

11km : turn to mela on to worli seaface.....the regular MRR hydration point.... Atria mall on right.

Run run till sea link at 16km....the other side of road will be like khumb mela with hmers. ( lots and lots of friends).

Turn on to sea link (only time in a year when it is open to public).....caution it's one of the most beautiful thing which happened to mumbai(please don't pee on or from this monument) . 

From 16 to 21 just enjoy and this were press photographers reside u may stand to be in news next day.

At 22kms u turn on to bandra mahim stretch.....you can see lot of people cheering for you.....slow runners like me gets the first realisation...
( half the distance more to cover)....
Mahim church and Mahim Dargah along......

24 kms : You move on......Hinduja hospital on right...you feel fine till now...
Now the iconic shivaji park and the land of spmc runners.....they will pamper u.....the Mayor's bungalow.....the chaitya bloomi..... the route of Mumbai ultra etc etc.....

This is where you realise a tornado effect......some aliens went past you....(the elite kenyans Ethiopians and Indians too).....I bow down to the èèee.....

26km...... Ganpati bappa morya..... hey siddhivinayaka .....give the strength to run remaining 16. 

27 Kms..... century mills on left and passport office on right....

28kms.....move on to worli seaface from RTO lane......(the most toughest part of fm begins).....

Looping on worliseaface.....you comeback.....INS Trata on left ( have served in Trata when in navy)....move on.....lots of volunteers.....you cramp.....the fight begins.....

At 32kms...... the thought "Why this  am I doing" "won't come back"......

At 34kms you are near race course and about to meet lata didi at peddar road she waiting with the song "yeh mere watan ke logo yaad karo qurbaani" and here we are not able to run.....

35kms.....welcome to peddar road residents association ......hats off to this guys ......they pamper you with every thing minus beer.....peddar road is over God.....

Some guys same as ur age will say this "uncle fast bhaago".....just turn back and say "uncle tera baap" ......

36kms.....turn on to babulnath and on to marine drive.....the King's bracelet begins.....

Now.....hallucinations begin....ur feet moves.....ur mind stops.....even you fail to notice a girls hostel on left near Wilson.....

At 38kms.....you can see dream runners enjoying and urging you to go fast.....police gymkhana on left....
At 40kms near Erst while jazz by the bay u turn towards last 2kms.....thats were Nana chudasama with his banner shines.....the last leg.....it seems even when the world amalgamate to make u stronger still you are down and cursing yourself for registering.

My favorite line goes through my mind "I run therefore I am"......a cop who is standing on morning duty from 0300 will feel....."saala u run therefore I am standing here".....

At 41kms......God am there.....

800 mtrs to go......wow....

600mtrs to go.....my brunch...

400mtrs to go.....my friends waiting....
On to the most iconic building on right.....the statue of Victoria smiling on u....

Mumbai embrace me.....

200mtrs..... the clock shows 5.26....
Last few steps......the clock shows 5.28.....

Finish line......eyes are wet and chest swells the dropping shoulder and the cramping legs give way.....to the stronger legs.....

Crossed .....5.28.04.....Rogered but dil bole ......will come back again next year.....earned the metal.....

At 43kms....who the hell put the ramp to climb.....idiot.......

-கணியன் பூங்குன்றனார்

Meet Namba Peter, since his childhood, He has been passionate about sports and nature. Endurance activities in the oudoors are his best way to nourish his soul, stay healthy ,fit and relax the mind. He loves long distance running in beautiful trails in the mountains. He recently hiked 3 months across 40 high altitude passes in the Himalayas. According to him, The beauty of nature and kindness of the people living in the mountains is beyond words.

His Two words of wisdow for endurance / dua- athletes - determination and patience will help you reach your goals. His Moment of change in life - when running was not no longer about numbers but about a way to travel and experience life.

He supports the cause of Aalam Deepam  Chennai Duathlon 2019...
To join and support for our cause Register @
https://www.eventjini.com/deepamduathlon2019

13/01/2019, 14:25 - +91 96770 88143: What is The 2019K Challenge?
The 2019K Challenge, is a challenge that you subscribe yourself to do 2019 km within the calendar year 2019. It is just to set a goal for yourself, so that, take this up as a challenge and try to achieve the goal, improve your running and improve your health.
 
Please Note: The 2019 Challenge requires you to run 2019 KM in 52 weeks or about 39 KM's each week. As such it is a good load for a rank beginner. 
 
If you have not been regular on your running and have not taken this kind of a load before then you should seriously reconsider scaling down your options. You can still be a part of the challenge and run a lesser distance.
 
We recommend 5 different flavours or approaches to accomplish the challenge. You can read about them by clicking on the link below.
 
To register & know more, click on the following link: http://bit.ly/ytcr2019challenge

20/01/2019, 14:12 - +91 99627 51544: My favorite place for running is at  amchi Mumbai
To start with,the weather was good and a flat course except 500 mtrs or so at pedar road. Unlike other cities, the road was clean and did not feel any discomfort throughout
running bare foot ( only socks to avoid pebbles)

Went flat out in the first 10 k and completed in 55.10 mnts and was very confident of doing a sub 2 hr finish.
Next 5 k took 30 mnts ( 15 k in 1 hr 27 mnts) and  still had 33 mnts for the final 6 km.
Decided not to look at my Garmin till the finish line and thought was going at comfortable pace but the final timing showed 2.03 hrs
Most satisfying factor was that  I did a non stop run from start to finish and 5 minutes gain from last year timing of 2.08 hrs.

I still feel young and will plan a sub 2  may be with in this year

24/01/2019, 20:32 - +91 99417 44342: An individual following a ketogenic diet will produce large amounts of acetone compared to those eating a high-carb diet.

When someone eats a high-fat and low carb diet or engaged in prolonged fasting, there isn’t enough glucose in the body for fuel. Therefore, the liver starts breaking down fatty acids for energy to fuel the body and the brain. This is the process known as ketosis, the primary function and goal of the ketogenic diet

29/01/2019, 18:57 - Badri Crpp: Here is the registration form for 52K. 
  
https://goo.gl/forms/Z1U8lR87MB0mO8Ij1.        

Welcome to the 2019 Edition of the "Val Vil Ori Ultra Marathon".   The run is scheduled for Sunday, March 17 2019.  
The Run will start at 4:00 AM from Nallathambi Resorts, Kolli Hills, Tamilnadu.  There will be two categories, 26K & 52K.

This registration form is only for those planning on running 52K.  

To run the 52K,  you must qualify by providing your recently (on or after 1-Aug-2018) completed Sub 5:30 full marathon or any Ultra (i.e. more than Full Marathon distance) within the cut-off timing for that event. 

After you furnish your details, you may be contacted regarding your eligibility to participate in the event.  Subject to approval (which is at the sole discretion of the organizers) you will get a confirmation email  regarding your entry.

This is an "at-cost" event that is funded entirely from the contributions from runners. A nominal fee of Rs 325 will be charged to confirmed participants.  Payment can be made on Saturday March 16 at Kolli Hills (further details on the event will be communicated via email, on our FB page https://www.facebook.com/groups/247679192078827/) and through a whatsapp group created for registered runners.  

52K Registration will close when the target of 50 runners is reached.

Any additional information needed - please shoot an email to - info@VVOUltra.in.

31/01/2019, 11:27 - Badri Crpp: https://www.townscript.com/e/chennaiultra-vvomrtb-043200

Here is the much awaited registration link for the 3rd Edition of the Chennai Ultra (formerly known as VV ultra).

The run will be hosted by Chennai Runners chapters of Vibrant Velachery (VV) and OMR Trail Blazers (OMRTB)

There will be two categories, 25k & 50K.

For 50km ultra,  the pre-requisite is to provide your link on the recently completed Full Marathon (on or after 01 Jan 2017) or any Ultra (i.e. more than Full Marathon distance)

Once the details are submitted, we will validate the registrations and will email you on confirmation of the same

This will be a road ultra and route will cover places across Velachery and OMR... you can be rest assured on runners getting wonderful support for the event.

The maximum allowable complicated running terms to be increased by 30% 

Finisher definition to include anyone who has finished either the marathon or breakfast

Those who earn more than 10 lakhs a year to sponsor 10 bibs for those who just run and don't earn

All medals will become digital and linked to aadhar card only with no chance of redemption

All trail runs to be free as they come under farm running

10% stress tax to be levied on all runners who post their PBs every time

All Sub 2 and sub 4 ( in HM and FM) to be considered under urban naxal tax

Anyone buying more than one pair of shoes every  2  years to be charged luxury tax

All runners who despite their best efforts are unable to increase mileage or improve timing will be deposited one marathon registration cost per month in their account

Anyone who uses more than 4 show off words in a running conversation will be eligible for election campaigning with non taxable income and permanently debarred from Marathons

Anyone who uses the word marathon for anything less than 21k will have all their assets seized immediately

14/02/2019, 12:17 - +91 89399 31625: As Posted by a Runner...
Last week, my wife went to Nirmal baba satsang.

Wife - Nirmalbabaki jai ho. Koti koti pranam
Nirmalbaba- kahan se aye ho? Kya pareshani hai?
W - Babaji, my husband.
N - What is the matter? Does he drink? Beats you? Has a girlfriend?
W - No babaji. He spends much money on running shorts, tees, energy gels, hydratiin belts, headband, wristband, calf sleeve, knee cap, dri-fit this, dri-fit that, supplements, pre-run drink, post-run drink, and many things i dont understand. I ask him to buy a saree, he has spent money on newest compression garment.
N - Anything else?
W - He registers for every running event every sunday. I am lucky, there are no marathons in evening, or he would have run one in morning, and another in evening. He never wins, but brings some metallic, heavy thing he calls a "medal", and will spend time cleaning, polishing them. Once i used a medal as a coster. He almost killed me
N - hmm
W - There's more. He never takes me out on saturdays, sundays or any other day. Interferes with his training, long run, intervals or some such s**t. He is so tired that he sleeps at 9.30 pm. You know! Cannot say more in public.
N- hmmm. Problem is very serious. Go and do darshan of sidhivinayak.
W - Babaji, he does that every month during the bandra-ncpa run
N - then go to shirdi.
W - Pshaw! I told him already, and he ran to shirdi with satish 
N - Then distribute some bananas, chocolates, idlis to poor people
W - That he already does, whenever he volunteers. 
N - Amma, your husband is a gone case. He has too much shakti, and my shakti is powerless 
W - Babaji, give some upay
N - there is one strong upay. I am not sure if you will be able to follow it
W - Babaji, I will do anything
N - Anything?
W  - Yes. Please tell
N-  You start running.

🗓Date: *24th February* 2019
📌

#Bhaaglo

#BharatKeVeer

This is a virtual run, you can 🏃🏻‍♀ 🏃🏻‍♂ 
Anywhere
Anytime
Any pace

Just record your run with App like Strava/Runkeeper/Runtastic/ Nike+ Run Club /Garmin/ Tomtom / Fitbit etc....
Any other marathon or running event result can be submitted as a proof in this event.

Data submission will be on www.indianrunners.in
*Automatic with Strava*
_Manually with other Apps_

09/03/2019, 17:54 - Sree Crpp: Dear Runners 
CR 13th Anniversary Run - 
Sunday 10th March.

1. Entrance - *Start and Finish point at Main Entrance Anna University at Sardar Patel Road* (same as last 2 years)

2. Please *do not enter via Kotturpuram side entrance* as there is another run conducted by the students of CEG and we want to avoid them

3. Route of 2.5kms loop inside Anna University. 2 loops for 5kms and 4 loops for 10kms.

4. Breakfast after the run.

5. Please ensure you have registered.

6. Kindly encourage Car Pooling to avoid parking congestion.
09/03/2019, 17:58 - Sree Crpp: *Sunday Run Schedule*

*Option 1*: CR Anniversary Run 

Venue: *Anna University*
Distance: 3k to 10k
Dress code : CRPP burgundy tee
4.30 am to 5.45am: Wrist Band collection (like bib collection)
5.45am : Warmup
6.00am : 10km Flag off
6.15am : 5km Flag off
6.45am : Breakfast Counters open
7.00am : Cake Cutting

*Option 2*
Start point : PGH 
Assembly Time: 5:00 am 
Start Time : 5:15 am 
Distance : 15 to 20k 
Route:
PGH to viveks and back (12k) 

*Option 3*: PGH to TTD and back(16k)  

Self Hydration  for option 2 and 3

Kindly text 'I'm in' by choosing the option and encourage others

12/03/2019, 05:46 - +91 98410 62632: https://www.goheritagerun.com/pench/?utm_source=athprofile&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=penchreminderall8mar

Run In India’s Premier Tiger Reserve And The Setting Of The Jungle Book this month - Go Heritage Run Pench! 

Pench is deep in the heart of Central India and yet quite convenient to get to from wherever you are in the country. Located in the Seoni and Chhindwara districts of Madhya Pradesh the main entrance to the Pench National Park is a short 2 hour drive away from Nagpur, which is well-connected by air and rail to the rest of the country. 

Seeonee is, of course, familiar to anyone who has read Rudyard Kipling's The Jungle Book. The book was set in the jungles of Central India and the precocious man-cub Mowgli - "stranger to man, friend of animals, brother of the wolves" - was raised by the Wolf Pack of these same Seeonee Hills. And so the Pench Tiger Reserve is the fictional home of Mowgli and his friends - Bagheera the Black Panther, Baloo the Bear, the Bandar-log, and of course Shere Khan, the tiger. 

You can expect to see these and other wildlife when you visit Pench this summer - sightings of tiger and other fauna are easier in the summer months as they flock to nearby water bodies. 

GO HERITAGE RUN - PENCH   
Date: Sunday, March 17th 2019
Distances: 5KM, 10KM, 21KM 
Venue: Pench National Park, Madhya Pradesh
Sign up: link

Note: This is a fun, untimed run and as this is an ecologically sensitive area, the run will be conducted in the buffer zone of the Pench National Park. 

Regards, 
Team GHR
Award-winning fun run series

16/03/2019, 16:39 - Gayatgri Mk: Dear all, new school session will begin soon. Now that you will buy new books, new bags, new pencil box, tiffinbox, bottles, new uniform & shoes. You will discard, old books, old dresses, Bag & bottle. You will either sell or dump somewhere all these stuffs, not to ever use again. 
Do you know, all these things which are scrap to you, can be useful and new for someone in need. Can bring smile on the face of so many. Need is of making it available to them.
 "Goonj" your close to heart organisation, under its "school to school" initiative, is happy to accept all exercise books, note books, loose papers, stationery, Water bottle, tiffin box, compass box, shoes, socks, slippers, uniforms, school bag, including old spectacles etc... everything which you feel are of no use to you, but will be useful to someone in need. Please come forward and contribute all you feel, will help to run a parallel life. 
Please contact Kavita Bansal on  9320009766.
A small request to please forward to all your groups. A small forward may bring a big smile on someone's face.
Goonj dropping centres all over India
Please refer http://goonj.org/page_id=22873/index.html for the same.

18/03/2019, 14:56 - Sree Crpp: Hi there everyone 
We are back with the 20th  edition of the – *CHENNAI RUNNERS MINNALS.LSoM*.13.1 #TheBestMilesofMadras on *Sunday, 31st March  2019* at 4:30 a.m. 

Starting and ending at the Lighthouse, you will run 21.1 km past a host of heritage monuments & beautiful landmarks along the breezy, scenic Marina Beach. This shall be a supported run with 5 aid stations serving water and some basic hydration & nutrition 
Please set a reminder for CR #MINNALS.LSoM.13.1 at 04:30 hours for last Sunday of this month on 31st March 2019, and stay tuned for further details! 

Hope to see our usual runners as well as encourage new runners to join this mega monthly event.

Thanks to volunteers from Marina Minnals & Pettai Rappers who are making this event more enjoyable and keeping us going with more editions to come monthly. As always, this edition is also free of cost for participants

Please do register. 

Route Link

In his excellent book, Stillpower, Sports Psychologist Garret Kramer says that a key factor to performing well in sports (and in life), is your ability to control the quality and quantity of your “internal dialogue”.

In other words, you need to stop yourself from *stopping yourself* 

Sports, fitness, business and indeed Life are played on a 6-inch ground … the space between our own two ears!

05/04/2019, 18:11 - +91 95001 21762: Mohan, not sure if you have gone through the rules. We have kept it very simple. You can run or workout on any day as per your plan. Irrespective of the distance you run or the activity you indulge in you get 1 point if you perform any run or cross training activity. 

W.r.to 66% - we want to encourage people to do group activity and motivate each other hence we have included that clause.. Here again it is not mandatory. We are rewarding groups that involve in group workouts. 

Lastly we debated extensively on tracking distance/speed etc and felt that it will encourage people to over do and cause more injuries and would be detrimental in the long run.. also tracking distance at individual level of specific days would make it super complex to administer.. 

As a case in point for tomorrow you may have few folks in your team cycling, few running and few doing stair workouts. Each of them will get 1 point + if you meet as a group at start or end and post group picture you also get bonus points for the group.  

As a philosophy we wanted to keep very less number of rules, and implement something that's very flexible, easy to follow and easy to administer..
